(Match 392)  7th April 1976  (Friendly match)
SCOTLAND - SWITZERLAND  1-0  (1-0)
Referee:   Patrick Partridge (England)
Crowd:     15.531, Hampden Park, Glasgow
Goal:      1-0 Pettigrew (2)
SCOTLAND:  (Manager:  William Esplin Ormond/31)
Alan Roderick Rough                (1/Partick Thistle) -
Daniel Fergus McGrain                              (25/Celtic)
Francis Tierney Gray                                         (1/Leeds United)
Thomas Forsyth [c]                                                (3/Rangers)
John Henderson Blackley                                                      (5/Hibernian) -
Thomas Brooks Craig                                                                             (1/Newcastle United)
Kenneth Mathieson Dalglish           (35/Celtic)
William H.Pettigrew                          (1/Motherwell) -
Andrew Mullen Gray                                               (2/Aston Villa)
Alexander MacDonald                                                            (1/Rangers)
Derek Johnstone                                                                              (8/Rangers)

Subs:
Robert Munro McKean                  (1/Rangers)    for William Pettigrew (46 Minutes)
Desmond George Bremner                                   (1/Hibernian)  for Kenneth Dalglish  (64 Minutes)

SWITZERLAND:  (Coach:  Rene Hussy)    
Erich Burgener - Gilbert Guyot, Jorg Stohler, Luciano Bizzini, Pius Fischbach - Kurt (Kudi)
Muller, Rene Hasler (Claude Andrey 53), Rene Botteron - Karl Elsener (Marc Schnyder 64), 
Peter Risi, Daniel Jeandupeux.
                   


